<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t16881205-15">
               <interp inst="t16881205-15" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16881205-15" type="year" value="1688"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16881205-15" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/16881205"></interp>
               <interp inst="t16881205-15" type="date" value="16881205"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t16881205-15-off63-c52" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-15-defend72 t16881205-15-off63 t16881205-15-verdict67"></join>
         
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t16881205-15-defend72" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Sibley
                  <interp inst="t16881205-15-defend72" type="surname" value="Sibley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-defend72" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-defend72" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was Tryed for <rs id="t16881205-15-off63" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-off63" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-off63" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               taking from the person of 
                     
                        <persName id="t16881205-15-victim74" type="victimName">
                           Elizabeth 
                           Cook
                        <interp inst="t16881205-15-victim74" type="surname" value="Cook"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16881205-15-victim74" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16881205-15-victim74" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-15-off63 t16881205-15-victim74"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                   Eight Lockets, composing a Bracelet, in the Parish of <placeName id="t16881205-15-crimeloc64">St. Christophers</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-crimeloc64" type="placeName" value="St. Christophers"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-crimeloc64" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-15-off63 t16881205-15-crimeloc64"></join>, on the <rs id="t16881205-15-cd65" type="crimeDate">8th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-15-off63 t16881205-15-cd65"></join> last, valued at 18 l.
            </rs> against whom 
               <persName id="t16881205-15-person75">
                  Elizabeth 
                  Cook
               <interp inst="t16881205-15-person75" type="surname" value="Cook"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-person75" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-person75" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             the Prosecutor deposed, That he the Prisoner came to her, and demanded to speak three words with her, and thereby took an opportunity to possess himself of the Lockets, by taking them from off her Arm: But it appearing that they had lived in a manner like Man and Wife, haing Things common between them; and that the Prisoner had been seen with the Lockets in his possession more than a year since: And upon the whole matter it appeared he had been a <rs id="t16881205-15-deflabel66" type="occupation">Servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16881205-15-defend72 t16881205-15-deflabel66"></join> of hers, whom she was desirous to shake off; so that finding the prosecution upon the Indictment of little weight, she desired of the Court, That she might charge him with an Action of 800 l. she pretended to be engaged with him for, or due to her. But that not being granted, the Jury, upon return of their Verdict, <rs id="t16881205-15-verdict67" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16881205-15-verdict67" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs> him of the Fact laid in the Indictment.</p>
            </div1>
